In the aftermath of Amadou Diallo's tragic death, protests erupted, leading to the arrest of 1,203 individuals.
Four white police officers were charged with murder for firing 41 bullets at the unarmed African immigrant.
The incident sparked a reevaluation of police tactics and race relations.
Diallo's parents met with the Bronx district attorney to discuss the impending charges.
Amid public outcry, the officers faced trial, with conflicting accounts of the events leading to Diallo's death.
The legal battle over forensic evidence and witness testimonies will be crucial in determining the officers' fate.
